goals.question: What is the distribution of miles driven per year?
goals.rationale: This visualization will help us understand the range of miles driven per year and identify any outliers.

goals.question: Is there a correlation between gas consumption and miles driven?
goals.visualization: Scatter plot of gas vs miles
goals.rationale: This visualization will help us identify if there is a relationship between gas consumption and miles driven. It can also help us identify any outliers.

goals.question: What is the average gas consumption per mile?
goals.visualization: Bar chart of gas per mile
goals.rationale: This visualization will help us understand the average gas consumption per mile and identify any trends or patterns.

goals.question: What is the distribution of gas consumption?
goals.rationale: This visualization will help us understand the range of gas consumption and identify any outliers.

goals.question: Is there a difference in gas consumption between different sides of the car?
goals.visualization: Box plot of gas by side
goals.rationale: This visualization will help us identify if there is a difference in gas consumption between the sides of the car and if there are any outliers.

code:
```
import seaborn as sns
import pandas as pd
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    sns.histplot(data=data, x='miles', color='blue')
    plt.axvline(data['miles'].mean(), color='red', linestyle='dashed', linewidth=1, label=f"Mean: {data['miles'].mean():.2f}")
    plt.axvline(data['miles'].median(), color='green', linestyle='dashed', linewidth=1, label=f"Median: {data['miles'].median():.2f}")
    plt.legend()
    plt.xticks(rotation=45)
    plt.title('What is the distribution of miles driven per year?', wrap=True)
    return plt

chart = plot(data)
```

import seaborn as sns
import pandas as pd
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    sns.set(style="whitegrid")
    chart = sns.barplot(x="year", y="gas_per_mile", data=data, color="b")
    chart.axhline(y=data['gas_per_mile'].mean(), color='r', linestyle='--', label='Mean')
    chart.legend(loc='upper left')
    return plt

chart = plot(data)
```

import seaborn as sns
import pandas as pd
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    sns.histplot(data=data, x='gas', kde=True, color='blue')
    plt.axvline(data['gas'].mean(), color='red', linestyle='dashed', linewidth=1, label=f'Mean: {data["gas"].mean():0.2f}')
    plt.axvline(data['gas'].median(), color='green', linestyle='dashed', linewidth=1, label=f'Median: {data["gas"].median():0.2f}')
    plt.legend()
    plt.title('What is the distribution of gas consumption?', wrap=True)
    plt.xlabel('Gas Consumption')
    plt.ylabel('Frequency')
    return plt

chart = plot(data)
```

import seaborn as sns
import pandas as pd
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    sns.set(style="whitegrid")
    ax = sns.boxplot(x="side", y="gas", data=data)
    ax.set_title("Is there a difference in gas consumption between different sides of the car?", wrap=True)
    ax.set_xlabel("Side of the car")
    ax.set_ylabel("Gas consumption")
    return plt

chart = plot(data)
